msgctxt "960"
msgid "Kokubu"
msgstr "Kokubu"

msgctxt "56_Kokubu"
msgid "So there's this yakuza tough named Midorikawa, right?\r\n"
"He and his pals controlled the theater underground."
msgstr "So there's this yakuza tough named Midorikawa, right?\r\n"
"He and his pals controlled the theater underground."

msgctxt "68_Kokubu"
msgid "They were up to all kinds of shady business down there...\r\n"
"that is, until a couple of days ago."
msgstr "Estaban haciendo todo tipo de negocios turbios ahí abajo...\r\n"
"es decir, hasta hace un par de días."

msgctxt "80_Kokubu"
msgid "This guy named Akiyama just strolls in and kicks 'em out.\r\n"
"He didn't look like much, but he gave Midorikawa's keester\r\n"
"the boot before any of those hooligans saw it coming."
msgstr "This guy named Akiyama just strolls in and kicks 'em out.\r\n"
"He didn't look like much, but he gave Midorikawa's keester\r\n"
"the boot before any of those hooligans saw it coming."

msgctxt "92_Kokubu"
msgid "Goes to show you can't judge a book by its cover...\r\n"
"and not all heroes wear capes."
msgstr "Lo que demuestra que no se puede juzgar un libro por su portada...y que no todos los héroes llevan capa."

